reviews.text: Nice dim sum place, fairly priced
Good taste, and they have English menu

Delicious dim sum, and also a la cart (小菜) too. Shrimp dumpling can be ordered by two pieces which is just perfect for couples. All dishes and dim sum were served steaming hot. Congee only served at dinner - very good. The only thing is, the BBQ pork buns are just ok. Very reasonable price and no service charge anytime, and accept credit card over $200 spending. Very friendly staff. Very good vibes. Spacious and clean, including toilets are clean too. 20% off afternoon tea time Mon to Sat. Open kitchen. A very pleasant experience dinning there.
